Jumia Food Nigeria has added one of the leading fresh food chain, So Fresh  to its catalogue of restaurants on its platform in a bid to promote healthy living among Nigerians. Addressing newsmen, the Managing Director of Jumia Food, Guy Futi said the Company’s commitment to promoting and encouraging a healthy lifestyle among Nigerians necessitated the partnership. With the partnership, he explained that customers can now order from So Fresh on Jumia Food. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE “We are always looking for new ways to serve our customers, such as through a partnership like this. I am particularly excited with So Fresh because, this is an opportunity for us to support and sustain healthy lifestyle among Nigerians through the consumption of fresh foods which customers can now order from So Fresh on Jumia Food . We remain focused on growing the business to become the largest on-demand platform in Nigeria,” Futi said. In his remarks, the Chief Executive Officer of So Fresh, Goke Balogun, said the partnership will help his company leverage Jumia Food’s visibility to grow the brand. According to him, So Fresh which was founded in 2010 as Fruitivegies but changed its name to So Fresh in 2013 currently has nine outlets in Lagos.  Over 11,000 entrepreneurs benefited from November sales – Jumia Jumia partners Pizza Hut in Lagos Jumia thrills consumers with 5 Black Fridays in November Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin